UNITED STATES of America v. Charlotte G. SHAW. No. 8365. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Jan. 18, 1940. Francis T. McDonald, U. S. Atty., and Joseph F. Deeb, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Grand Rapids, Mich., for appellant. Knappen, Uhl, Bryant & Snow, of Grand Rapids, Mich., for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed pursuant to stipulation of counsel.
